column1: 7090 new COVID-19 cases reported today in the Badger State. Wisconsin workers can't wait for OSHA to do its job.   Commonsense measures like my "COVID-19 Every Worker Protection Act" are what we need to protect our workforce during this deadly pandemic.   https://t.co/h22rf4jIDm

COVID cases are skyrocketing in Wisconsin yet Donald Trump has said the country is “rounding the corner.” I don’t know what “corner” he’s talking about. Nine months in and Trump still has no plan to get this virus under control. — TB #Debates2020

Had the pleasure of chatting with @debforwi and Beth a small business owner and mom in Whitefish Bay today. We discussed Wisconsin's economy and how @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris have a plan to combat COVID-19 and #BuildBackBetter. — TB https://t.co/ru7RuEtLVe
